<h2 id="motivation">Motivation</h2>

<p>I want to install Scala on my PC.</p>

<h2 id="preparation">Preparation</h2>

<p>I read <a href="https://docs.scala-lang.org/">Scalaâ€™s documentation</a>.</p>

<h2 id="method">Method</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Install Java as explained in <a href="https://largecats.github.io/2019/07/31/install-spark-on-windows/">this post</a>.</li>
  <li>Install Scala (without sbt) from <a href="https://downloads.lightbend.com/scala/2.13.0/scala-2.13.0.msi">here</a>.</li>
  <li>Create a system variable <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">SCALA_HOME</code> and set it to the path of the Scala installation.</li>
  <li>Add <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">%SCALA_HOME%\jre\bin</code> to path.</li>
  <li>Open <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">cmd</code> and type <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">scala</code>. The output should look something like this.
    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> C:\Users\steve-rogers&gt;scala
 Welcome to Scala 2.13.0 (Java HotSpot(TM) Client VM, Java 1.8.0_221).
 Type in expressions for evaluation. Or try :help.

 scala&gt;
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
</ol>
